name: Low-Carb Keto Cheese Taco Shells
author: Fioa
summary: Try these cheese taco shells made from baked Cheddar cheese and shaped into a taco; these are a great gluten-free, low-carb, and keto option.
directions: Preheat oven to 400 degrees F (200 degrees C)
Line 2 baking sheets with parchment paper or silicone mats
Wrap the handle of a wooden spoon with aluminum foil
Spread Cheddar cheese on the prepared baking sheets into four 6-inch circles placed 2 inches apart
Bake in the preheated oven until cheese melts and is lightly brown, 6 to 8 minutes
Lift with a spatula and drape over the wrapped wooden handle; cool until set, about 10 minutes
